<p>Drop frames and speed gif up with <a href="https://www.lcdf.org/gifsicle/">gifsycle</a> (via <a href="https://graphicdesign.stackexchange.com/a/20937">How to remove every second frame from an animated gif?</a>):</p>
<pre><code class="language-bash">gifsicle -U in.gif `seq -f &quot;#%g&quot; 0 3 398` -O2 -o out.gif
</code></pre>
<p>ps. 398 is the total number of frames, which you can get with:</p>
<pre><code class="language-bash">identify in.gif
</code></pre>
